<HEADLINE>
THREE DRUG 'MULES' ARRESTED AT TAOYUAN INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, March 21 (CNA) 03/21/07  22:01:34 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
Three drug "mules" were arrested Wednesday at Taoyuan
International Airport when they returned from overseas trips,
said a spokesman for the Criminal Investigation Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman told reporters that two of the three heroin
carriers, identified by their surnames as Chao and Lin, were
taken into custody as they returned from Macao, while the third
carrier, who is also surnamed Lin, was arrested as he returned
from Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, all three carried condom-wrapped
heroin balls in their rectums. They were sent to Min Sheng
Hospital in Taoyuan, where medical personnel removed 15 heroin
balls weighing 0.92 kg in total.
</P>
<P>
Two other men, surnamed Lin and Hsieh, who paid the heroin
carriers to smuggle the drug, were also arrested at the airport.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the three mules will be referred to the Public
Prosecutor's Office in Taipei for prosecution, while the two men
who hired the carriers to do the jobs will be charged at the
Keelung District Public Prosecutors' Office.
</P>
